    <briefdescription>
<para>High-speed binary telemetry logger. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Captures arbitrary structs or data frames into a static ringbuffer. Useful for high-speed PID tuning, state recording, or telemetry streams.</para>
<para>Uses a zero-allocation, lock-free ringbuffer backend. Data is prefixed with a 16-bit ID and 16-bit length to allow demultiplexing on the host. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
